rComments: Stellar.  A really nice and funny guy. Goes off on tangents though.

Lectures were always interesting and amusing, prof has a great sense of humour, but he would often get sidetracked.  Liked to introduce a great deal of econ theory into lectures, which was difficult if you don't have an econ background. But though I felt a bit lost during lectures, by the end of the year I had an excellent understanding of contract
Difficult prof, but I would take a class with him just so I can look at him.
puts in serious effort and has great energy; explanations could be clearer at times, though the material is inherently difficult so this inevitable; will be a *star* in a couple years...
puts good effort in, but still isn't quite comfortable.  a young wine, needs some time in the barrel to mature
I think people need to calm down about the "hotness" claim - he is okay, but nothing to sweat about. As a prof, he needs some work... i would say give him a few years.
Prof Alarie is amazing.  Brilliant, articulate, humble, and most of all, HOT.  I heard his brother is even cooler...If true, I'd offer to have his children.
